cardano/address/Address.title: Address
cardano/address/Address.description:
A Cardano `Address` typically holding one or two credential references.

 Note that legacy bootstrap addresses (a.k.a. 'Byron addresses') are
 completely excluded from Plutus contexts. Thus, from an on-chain
 perspective only exists addresses of type 00, 01, ..., 07 as detailed
 in [CIP-0019 :: Shelley Addresses](https://github.com/cardano-foundation/CIPs/tree/master/CIP-0019/#shelley-addresses).

cardano/address/Credential.title: Credential
cardano/address/Credential.description:
A general structure for representing an on-chain `Credential`.

 Credentials are always one of two kinds: a direct public/private key
 pair, or a script (native or Plutus).

cardano/address/PaymentCredential.title: PaymentCredential
cardano/address/PaymentCredential.description:
A general structure for representing an on-chain `Credential`.

 Credentials are always one of two kinds: a direct public/private key
 pair, or a script (native or Plutus).

cardano/address/StakeCredential.title: StakeCredential
cardano/address/StakeCredential.description:
Represent a type of object that can be represented either inline (by hash)
 or via a reference (i.e. a pointer to an on-chain location).

 This is mainly use for capturing pointers to a stake credential
 registration certificate in the case of so-called pointer addresses.

cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

psi_research/redeemers/PoolRedeemer.title: PoolRedeemer
psi_research/redeemers/PoolRedeemer.description: Actions for the research contribution pool

anyOf.title: Contribute
anyOf.description:
Add funds to the research pool
 Called automatically when experiments settle

anyOf.title: Withdraw
anyOf.description: Withdraw funds from pool (requires governance multi-sig)

anyOf.title: UpdateGovernance
anyOf.description: Update governance committee (requires current governance approval)

psi_research/redeemers/PsiRedeemer.title: PsiRedeemer
psi_research/redeemers/PsiRedeemer.description:
Redeemers for PsyApp Psi-Research Smart Contracts
 All possible actions that can be taken on session UTxOs
 All possible actions on a session UTxO

anyOf.title: Join
anyOf.description:
Player joins the session and locks matching stake
 Submits hash of their guess (commit phase)

anyOf.title: Reveal
anyOf.description:
Host reveals the target value and nonce
 Triggers winner determination and settlement

anyOf.title: SubmitScore
anyOf.description:
For scored experiments - submit AI/oracle evaluation
 Only valid for RemoteViewing, EmotionEcho, PatternOracle

anyOf.title: RevealGuess
anyOf.description:
Player reveals their actual guess (for commit-reveal)
 Used in some game modes where participant also commits

anyOf.title: Settle
anyOf.description:
Claim funds after successful reveal and settlement
 Called to finalize distribution

anyOf.title: ClaimHostTimeout
anyOf.description:
Claim timeout: Host failed to reveal in time
 Participant gets their stake back + host's stake (minus research %)

anyOf.title: ClaimParticipantTimeout
anyOf.description:
Claim timeout: No one joined in time
 Host gets their stake back

anyOf.title: MutualCancel
anyOf.description:
Emergency cancel with both parties signing
 Each party gets their stake refunded

anyOf.title: ClaimReward
anyOf.description: Participant claims Psy tokens during game settlement

anyOf.title: TopUp
anyOf.description: Admin deposits additional Psy tokens

anyOf.title: UpdateParams
anyOf.description: Admin adjusts decay parameters

psi_research/reward_types/RewardVaultDat.title: RewardVaultDatum
psi_research/reward_types/RewardVaultDat.description:
Datum for the Psy token reward vault
 Tracks decay parameters and claim count for hyperbolic reward distribution
